==English==
{{wp|ARE}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|aren}}, from {{inh|en|ang|earun}}, {{m|ang|earon|t=are}}, reinforced by {{cog|non|-}} plural forms in {{m|non||er-}} (displacing alternative {{cog|ang|sind}} and {{m|ang|bēoþ}}), from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*arun|t=(they) are}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|[[*esi]]/[[*izi]]}} (a form of {{der|en|gem-pro|*wesaną|t=to be}}), from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*h₁ésti|t=is}}.

Cognate with {{cog|non|eru|t=(they) are}} (> {{cog|is|eru|t=(they) are}}, {{cog|sv|äro|t=(they) are}}, {{cog|da|er|t=(they) are}}), {{cog|ang|eart|t=(thou) art}}. More at {{l|en|art}}.

====Alternative forms====
* {{alter|en|aren|arn||obsolete or dialectal}}
* {{alter|en|ar||obsolete}}

